Advances have been made in the function call department.

The target language is now functional. The parameters of function calls substitute their analogs in the function declaration.
And the function declaration with the variables names already substituted goes on to substitute the function call.

This leads to the following examples:



int main(void);
int aRandomMathOperation(int);

int aRandomMathOperation(int a){
    return a + 1 * 2 + 3;
}

int main(int z){

    double y = 0, x = 1;


    aRandomMathOperation(x);


}

int xx = 1 * 2 + 3;
int z = 0;
z = aRandomMathOperation(xx);
z = main(z);


